text=[[#excerpt]]%0aThis question establishes the metric or measure of achieving the outcome. This is how the client wants to receive the outcome. Press here for business metrics, to go along with the business reasons established in WhatWillThatGetForYou.%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0aThis question is best asked from the ''future'' DesiredState: %0a%0a->"When you first had ''d(n)'', how did you recognize it?"%0a%0a''d(n)'' represents the sequence of desired states. The current state is ''d(0)'', although most likely the current state is not "desired". It can be useful to stage the [[future desired state -> DesiredState]] in order to help the client see that what they want can be achieved in stages, and that what they want now might not be their end goal.%0a%0a(:if false:)%0aSummary:to establish (and help) the client's understanding of when they have arrived at the desired state%0aParent:(Consulting.)PrecisionInquiry%0aIncludeMe:[[Consulting.PrecisionInquiry]]%0aCategories:[[!Articles]]%0aTags: consulting, elicitation, precision inquiry, questions%0a(:tags-hide  consulting, elicitation, precision inquiry, questions:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a
